# Jacked in June 2026 — Cursor Project Rules

## Project Overview

Static GitHub Pages site for IMW's "Jacked in June" Iron Man fitness challenge.
- Submissions via Power Automate → OneDrive Excel or SharePoint List (see docs/microsoft-setup.md)

## Tech Stack

- Vanilla HTML / CSS / JavaScript (no build step)
- GitHub Pages for hosting
- Google Apps Script for form backend

## Conventions

- Keep the site static — no npm/build tooling unless explicitly requested
- Images live in `assets/images/` (web copies) and `site assets/images/` (originals)
- Activity points and team data are defined in `js/activities.js`
- Form submission endpoint is in `js/activities.js` as `FORM_ENDPOINT`
- Match existing IMW branding: mountain background, white IMW logo, blue/gold accent palette

## Key Files

- `index.html` — main page (hero, point guide, tracker form)
- `css/styles.css` — all styles
- `js/activities.js` — activity config, teams, point math
- `js/app.js` — UI logic, session management, form submit

## When Editing

- Update year/branding consistently across HTML and README
- Test point calculations when changing activity definitions
- Preserve field names: Timestamp, Team, Member, Activity, DurationMinutes, Steps, Points
